# PurserPay — environment template. Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored; only this example
# is tracked). The values below are a READY-TO-USE LOCAL DEVELOPMENT setup.
#
# ============================================================================
#  LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (the default — `cp .env.local.example .env.local` just works)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  `npm run db:start` boots a LOCAL Supabase (Docker); the URL + keys below point at it.
#  localhost then runs on Nile against that local DB — it can NEVER touch the production
#  Supabase project. Isolation is physical, not disciplinary. (See docs/06 §1, docs/04 §5.)
#  For PRODUCTION, set the counterpart values in the Vercel dashboard — the notes on each
#  var say what changes.
# ============================================================================

# --- Public: inlined into the client bundle (NEXT_PUBLIC_*) ------------------
# LOCAL: the local Supabase stack. PROD: your https://<project-ref>.supabase.co.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# LOCAL: the well-known Supabase local demo anon JWT (issuer "supabase-demo") — PUBLIC, not a
# secret, identical on every local install (`npm run db:status` prints it). Protected by RLS.
# PROD: your project's anon / publishable key.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZS1kZW1vIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJleHAiOjE5ODM4MTI5OTZ9.CRXP1A7WOeoJeXxjNni43kdQwgnWNReilDMblYTn_I0

# THE build-time network seam (src/lib/tron/config.ts): "mainnet" | "nile".
# Selects the whole chain block (network + PurserPay contract address + USDT token) at BUILD
# time — client and server (serverRead.ts) read the same resolved value, so they can never
# target different networks. REQUIRED: config.ts THROWS at module load if missing/unrecognized
# (fail closed). There is deliberately NO runtime toggle. LOCAL = nile (local Supabase);
# PRODUCTION = mainnet (production Supabase) — the only two environments (docs/06 §1). Every
# non-mainnet build also renders the SANDBOX banner.
NEXT_PUBLIC_TRON_NETWORK=nile

# --- Server-only: never inlined into the client (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix) ------
# LOCAL: the local demo service_role JWT (bypasses RLS; only used server-side via
# src/lib/supabase/server.ts). PROD: your project's service_role / secret key. Never ship to client.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZS1kZW1vIiwicm9sZSI6InNlcnZpY2Vfcm9sZSIsImV4cCI6MTk4MzgxMjk5Nn0.EGIM96RAZx35lJzdJsyH-qQwv8Hdp7fsn3W0YpN81IU

# Global pepper for wallet-address hashing (src/lib/crypto.ts → hashWalletAddress). Server-only.
# ⚠ MUST DIFFER between local and production — this is a CORRECTNESS invariant, not a preference.
# The compliance tables key on `wallet_hash = hash(address, WALLET_SALT)` with NO network
# dimension. If local and prod share this salt, the hashes COLLIDE: a testnet payout on localhost
# computes the SAME wallet_hash a mainnet customer will — so even against a separate database it
# would target a real customer's row. The value below is a FRESH, DEV-ONLY salt (safe to share
# across dev machines; it just must never equal production's). Generate your own with:
#   openssl rand -hex 32
# NEVER copy production's WALLET_SALT here.
WALLET_SALT=3feecddb39f8785eb0bd3614f4671fad6213da443c56351f8d0687e2310f5555

# AES key for pgcrypto encryption of account-holder PII (billing_profiles.encrypted_pii).
# Server-only; passed to the encrypt_and_store_pii RPC per call, never stored in the DB, never
# exposed to the client. Rotating it makes existing ciphertext undecryptable — permanent once PII
# exists. Below is a FRESH, DEV-ONLY key; production must use its own. Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
PII_ENCRYPTION_KEY=5f49a32aa9b2257da9882f8682c20d811febcaedb472be9816adee94a2688083

# TronGrid API key for the server-side reads the payout gate makes (isSubscriptionActive +
# txid re-verification in src/lib/tron/serverRead.ts). Server-only.
#   - Nile (LOCAL): OPTIONAL. Leave unset to read without a key.
#   - MAINNET (PROD): REQUIRED. Without it TronGrid rate-limits these reads → readSubscriptionActive()
#     returns null → the gate fails CLOSED and a PAYING customer sees the paywall. serverRead.ts
#     THROWS at boot on a mainnet build if this is missing (fail loud, never silent at a payday).
# (Also: the deploy scripts require it on mainnet — a keyless mainnet deploy/read 429s.)
# TRON_PRO_API_KEY=<trongrid-api-key>

# Referral kill switch (src/lib/referral/config.ts). Server-only (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix).
# DEFAULT OFF: the reward mechanic + the dashboard referral card stay dark until this is
# truthy ("1"/"true"/"yes"/"on"). Attribution (/r/{code} cookie) and honoring already-earned
# credit run regardless — only GRANTING new rewards is gated. Leave unset to keep it off.
REFERRALS_ENABLED=true
